-I want to show something.

302
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:07,380
This is the first cup, Auau already stirred it.

303
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:10,740
But for the other cups, Auau, you need to peel them.

304
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:15,500
This pineapple's huge, I'll handle it myself.

305
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:18,620
See? We can make non-alcoholic cocktails!

306
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:21,740
How much time's left? Check the clock for me!

307
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:24,260
Three minutes?

308
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:25,860
Auau, Auau, I got it!

309
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:28,380
This won't work, it's not firm enough.

310
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:29,300
We need to squeeze, squeeze!

311
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,820
-Come on.
-Go wash your hands first.

312
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:32,580
Are you serious?

313
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:33,940
Don't.

314
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,660
Have you seen...

315
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:40,340
-Please don't put this down.
-No, no, no. Don't rush.

316
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:43,740
-No, don't put this. This is mine.
-Don't.

317
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:45,540
I won't let you put it.

318
00:13:45,540 --> 00:13:47,540
It's already beautiful, Auau!

319
00:13:47,540 --> 00:13:49,020
Can I set aside the one I'll drink?

320
00:13:52,140 --> 00:13:53,420
We should wipe the cups to make them look nice.

321
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:56,580
-Is this all that's left? It was full before.
-No, some spilled.

322
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:01,500
Don't regret it.

323
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,860
This pineapple juice must be super salty!

324
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:06,420
No one wants it. Auau, you take it!

325
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:10,260
Auau, why not take it out too?
Only the three of us know, let the others drink it!

326
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:13,500
-10, 9, 8.
-It's really fun. -It's fun.

327
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:16,540
-Done!
-Put something in to mark it so we don’t drink it.

328
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:20,460
-5 4 3
-Auau, our mark's fading!

329
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:21,980
-Forget it.
-It's... -2.

330
00:14:21,980 --> 00:14:23,100
-Let it be. Auau's done.
-1.

331
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:24,100
-Oh my.
-0.

332
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:26,460
-Woohoo!
-Time’s up!

333
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,940
-We made good use of our time.
-Yes.

334
00:14:28,940 --> 00:14:30,700
Because we had time to play.

335
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:33,380
We washed them. Everything's clean, guys!
-Washed, washed!

336
00:14:33,380 --> 00:14:34,980
This cup's been washed too.

337
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:38,980
Let's see who the lucky one is!

338
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:40,100
Who will drink this?

339
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,420
-Yes, because...
-We'll keep it a secret.

340
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:47,980
Right now, only me, Kong, and Auau know this cup is special.

341
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:49,180
But Kong, you absolutely can't tell the others!

342
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:50,500
-You can't say.
-I won't tell anyone.

343
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,700
-Okay.
-Okay.

344
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:53,100
Okay, it's done. Let's go.

345
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,660
Let's go. Let's go.

346
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:58,620
[Non-alcoholic cocktails]

347
00:15:02,260 --> 00:15:05,460
Okay, we're the last group.

348
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:06,180
Okay, come on.

349
00:15:06,180 --> 00:15:08,180
Today, we're making fried eggs with minced pork.

350
00:15:08,180 --> 00:15:11,380
-Shall we start?
-Go ahead, bro, you start, I'll watch.

351
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:13,860
First, we need to take out the stove.

352
00:15:13,860 --> 00:15:15,380
Oh, the stove.

353
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:16,540
The stove.

354
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:17,860
Okay.

355
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:18,540
Hey.

356
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:19,780
This is our stove.

357
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:22,220
This is how it works!

358
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:23,660
-Hey.
-Okay.

359
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:25,900
We need to wash our hands first.

360
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,780
-I already washed my hands.
-Then I'll go wash.

361
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:31,940
Tho, come crack the eggs for us!

362
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:33,500
No, I don't know how to crack eggs!

363
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,500
-No, really, you can do it.
-I really can't.

364
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,100
-Come on, show us.
-I'll show that I can't.

365
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:38,340
Then can I teach you?

366
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:40,140
Knock here.

367
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:41,660
Tap once.

368
00:15:41,660 --> 00:15:43,300
Then separate the eggshell.

369
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:46,700
And then...

370
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,260
Tho.

371
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:52,780
-I told you I can't do it.
-It's not like this.

372
00:15:57,620 --> 00:15:59,460
The egg's too sticky!

373
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:01,740
-You need to pick it out.
-So you're just like me!

374
00:16:01,740 --> 00:16:04,860
Everyone, let's see if Kong can get the eggshell out today!

375
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:06,820
Ah, he's picked out one piece.

376
00:16:06,820 --> 00:16:08,380
One more piece left, the last one!

377
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:11,700
-Finally.
-You picked it out, Kong, good job.

378
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,700
-Hmm?
-How many eggs do we need?

379
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,340
Uh, let's do 5 then.

380
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:17,860
-Okay.
-Okay.

381
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,420
-Tho, you keep going.
-Wait for me a sec.

382
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:26,140
I've seen people beat eggs with one hand, how do they do it?

383
00:16:26,140 --> 00:16:27,220
I can't beat eggs with one hand.

384
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,820
-I'll show you.
-Let's do it.

385
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:44,820
Hey.

386
00:16:44,820 --> 00:16:46,820
Tho, you pick it out.

387
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:47,900
It fell in again!

388
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,540
-Come here.
-Here.

389
00:16:49,540 --> 00:16:51,780
Look, everyone, this is beating eggs with one hand!

390
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:54,740
This is my first time beating an egg with one hand!

391
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:57,060
How's it going? Did you get it out?

392
00:16:57,060 --> 00:16:58,900
Thank you.

393
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,900
-What is this?
-This one.

394
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:04,380
Fish sauce.

395
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:08,260
Didn't you see my face just now?

396
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:12,980
You won't add too much, right?

397
00:17:12,980 --> 00:17:14,339
Not much, there are lots of eggs.

398
00:17:14,339 --> 00:17:17,099
OK, Kong, let me show you how to beat eggs.

399
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:21,060
-I've been cooking since I was little.
-You mean playing house?

400
00:17:21,060 --> 00:17:23,060
-How did you know?
-Uh, playing house.

401
00:17:23,060 --> 00:17:25,060
-Wow.
-Smell it, does it smell good?

402
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,300
Fishy smell.

403
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:30,580
It’s fine, let's focus on the final dish.

404
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:32,380
Are we adding the minced pork now?

405
00:17:37,580 --> 00:17:39,460
Like this, Tho, see?

406
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:41,860
And then?

407
00:17:41,860 --> 00:17:44,620
Then we need to stir the eggs evenly.

408
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:46,180
Will the pork be cooked?

409
00:17:46,180 --> 00:17:47,300
Yes.

410
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:50,300
Today's dish isn't fried eggs with minced pork!

411
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:54,460
It's minced pork with fried eggs, the pork's the star!

412
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:57,140
We should fill it up with this.

413
00:17:57,140 --> 00:17:58,540
Okay, go ahead.

414
00:17:58,540 --> 00:18:00,540
-I’ll turn on the stove for you.
-Okay, Tho, add the oil directly.

415
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:01,740
How do I turn it on?

416
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:05,460
There's a button.

417
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:09,300
Oh, you need to press a button to start the fire.

418
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,140
Guys.

419
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:12,780
-Good job.
-Good job.

420
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:16,020
Let's wait for the pan to heat up.

421
00:18:16,020 --> 00:18:20,220
-Then let's chat for now.
-Ah, sure.

422
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:24,820
Uh, after finishing Your Sky, what're your thoughts, Kong?

423
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:25,900
-Me?
-Yes.

424
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:31,100
I feel like I'd want to try being Muenfah.

425
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,500
What did you just say?

426
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:33,980
I want to be Muenfah.

427
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:35,500
Why?

428
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:38,060
I just...

429
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:41,100
I want to talk less.

430
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:43,620
Let's see if we can add it now.

431
00:18:44,780 --> 00:18:46,140
-Oh, it’s time, it's time.
-It's ready, should we add it?

432
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:46,780
Come on.

433
00:18:46,780 --> 00:18:47,660
Tho, you add it!

434
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:49,620
You do it, Kong.

435
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,220
-Are you scared?
-I'm not scared

436
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,820
Put it in.

437
00:18:56,740 --> 00:18:58,180
Oh, Kong, be careful!

438
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:08,380
Okay.

439
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:13,780
Wow, you're amazing.

440
00:19:13,780 --> 00:19:16,860
Hmm, you can smell the food now.

441
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,260
It's not ready yet, right?

442
00:19:19,860 --> 00:19:22,460
Or are you just moving the edges?

443
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:26,620
But can you teach us how to make fried eggs properly?

444
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:29,660
Am I doing it right? I've never made fried eggs myself.

445
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:30,660
-Really?
-Really.

446
00:19:30,660 --> 00:19:32,620
But I think you're doing great!

447
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:38,540
Ah, then let's chat while we wait.

448
00:19:38,540 --> 00:19:39,580
-Okay.
-Ah.

449
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:42,300
I've got a question for you, chef.

450
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:47,300
How many years of cooking experience do you have?

451
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:50,740
Whoa, I've been cooking since I was born!

452
00:19:50,740 --> 00:19:51,700
Since birth, huh?

453
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:54,260
Right from when I came out of my mom's belly.

454
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,060
Yes.

455
00:19:55,060 --> 00:19:56,100
Uh.

456
00:19:57,820 --> 00:19:59,820
What was the first dish you made?

457
00:19:59,820 --> 00:20:03,460
Something like panna cotta.

458
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:06,140
Panna cotta's an Italian dish.

459
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:07,780
-Yes.
-No, it's French.

460
00:20:09,220 --> 00:20:10,340
Are you kidding me?

461
00:20:10,340 --> 00:20:14,100
One thing you've got to get right is...

462
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:16,620
the eggs cook faster than the pork.

463
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:20,140
The pork'll burn first, no, the eggs'll burn first.

464
00:20:20,140 --> 00:20:22,380
And the pork might not cook through.

465
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:23,060
Ah.

466
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:26,060
This stove's fire is super strong!

467
00:20:26,060 --> 00:20:27,220
The strongest in the world.

468
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:28,220
-Really?
-Yes.

469
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:30,860
-What should we do next?
-Three minutes left.

470
00:20:30,860 --> 00:20:31,860
Okay.

471
00:20:31,860 --> 00:20:32,500
Is there enough time?

472
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:36,540
No worries, we just wait
for the meat to cook, that's it, super easy!

473
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:37,740
Very simple.

474
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:38,580
Oh.

475
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:41,500
Making fried eggs is really easy!

476
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:42,780
No challenge at all!

477
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:45,780
At first, I thought we'd be making
Beef Wellington or something.

478
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:48,540
Bring it here, Tho. I think it's ready.

479
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:52,380
Of course.

480
00:20:54,140 --> 00:20:55,340
Bring me the plate.

481
00:20:55,340 --> 00:20:57,740
Why not just pour it out like this?

482
00:20:57,740 --> 00:20:59,980
There's a lot of oil, I don't want to pour that too.

483
00:21:00,820 --> 00:21:03,940
-No, it's already cut, if it were whole, we could flip it.
-Okay, alright, no problem.

484
00:21:03,980 --> 00:21:05,180
Give me a hand.

485
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:06,780
Let's call it pizza.

486
00:21:07,420 --> 00:21:08,100
Yes.

487
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:12,020
Okay, here's the final step.

488
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:13,580
Let's decorate it.

489
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:15,580
-Let's draw a cat. Tho, what do you want?.
-Cat, then cat it is.

490
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:17,460
-I, I just want...
-Let's draw together.

491
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:20,060
-Tho, follow me. I know how to draw it.
-Okay.

492
00:21:21,860 --> 00:21:23,460
Kong, use some strength.

493
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,060
Like this.

494
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:28,500
More.

495
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,300
-Oh.
-Hey.

496
00:21:31,180 --> 00:21:33,220
Not so close!

497
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:38,020
-Okay.
-Are you okay?

498
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:40,020
How do we draw the tail here? A curly tail?

499
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:41,700
Wait, draw a circle from here.

500
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:47,260
Oh, I touched it.

501
00:21:47,260 --> 00:21:48,340
Hey, I saw coriander.

502
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:51,500
-Don't forget the cat's head.
-What're you saying?

503
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,540
Is he calling us?

504
00:21:55,460 --> 00:21:57,300
-He just called us.
-Oh.

505
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:58,340
Oh.

506
00:21:58,340 --> 00:21:59,180
Oh.

507
00:21:59,180 --> 00:21:59,940
Where'd this come from?

508
00:21:59,940 --> 00:22:01,660
How do we use this to decorate?

509
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:04,420
Time's up.

510
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:06,620
-Hey.
-Put it down. Hands up like a chef.

511
00:22:06,620 --> 00:22:08,900
-Hands up like a chef.
-Okay. Okay.

512
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:11,740
Uh, hands up to show we're done.

513
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,620
We're out of time, Tho, so we need to plate it first.

514
00:22:15,620 --> 00:22:18,940
This dish is our fried eggs.

515
00:22:18,940 --> 00:22:20,220
It's fried eggs with minced pork.

516
00:22:20,220 --> 00:22:22,100
But we have more pork than fried eggs.

517
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,660
-Yes, so it's minced pork with fried eggs.
-Hmm, minced pork with fried eggs.

518
00:22:24,660 --> 00:22:27,220
It's not fried eggs. There's something wrong with the ingredients.

519
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:29,500
This is minced pork with fried eggs added.

520
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,660
No, we wanted it to be special.

